{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840771010,"sessionID":"ses_287a765acffeRk0Us3p2NYXBMa","part":{"id":"prt_d78599f39001xCpNjXHvcpOgmt","messageID":"msg_d78598d74001gSNB7OH0WsfxPH","sessionID":"ses_287a765acffeRk0Us3p2NYXBMa","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-002  \n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small  \n\nDefine the Go type definitions for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets safely within Kubernetes.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\nThe CodeInterpreter type extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    Kubernetes API Server                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1                  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ AgentRuntimeв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ         CodeInterpreter         в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ             в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ CodeInterpreterSpec       в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Image   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Image (required)        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Resourcesв”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Language (enum)         в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Ports   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Resources (optional)    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ ...     в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - TimeoutSeconds          в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - MaxMemoryMB             в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ             в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Env                     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Status  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ Phase   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ CodeInterpreterStatus     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ ...     в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Phase (enum)            в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - Conditions              в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - SandboxID               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                   в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ - ExecutionCount          в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                   в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                              в”Ӯ\n                              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    Generated client-go                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Clientset     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    Informers    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    Listers      в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                 в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ В· Interface     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ В· SharedInformerв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ В· Lister        в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ В· Create/Get/...в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Factory       в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ В· NamespaceList в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ В· Per-type      в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                       в”Ӯ   informers     в”Ӯ                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                       в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                      в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n1. **Type Definitions** (`codeinterpreter_types.go`): Go structs with kubebuilder markers\n2. **Scheme Registration** (`register.go`): Adds types to the runtime scheme\n3. **Code Generation**: `controller-gen` generates DeepCopy methods; `code-generator` creates client-go\n4. **Client Consumers**: Workload Manager, CLI tools, external controllers\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### CodeInterpreterPhase\n\nEnumeration representing the lifecycle phases of a CodeInterpreter.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CodeInterpreterPhase string\n\nconst (\n    // CodeInterpreterPhasePending indicates the interpreter is being provisioned.\n    CodeInterpreterPhasePending CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning indicates the interpreter is active and ready.\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded indicates the interpreter completed successfully.\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed indicates the interpreter failed.\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n)\n```\n\n#### ProgrammingLanguage\n\nEnumeration of supported programming languages with validation.\n\n```go\n// ProgrammingLanguage represents a supported programming language.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go;rust;java;cpp\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype ProgrammingLanguage string\n\nconst (\n    LanguagePython     ProgrammingLanguage = \"python\"\n    LanguageJavaScript ProgrammingLanguage = \"javascript\"\n    LanguageTypeScript ProgrammingLanguage = \"typescript\"\n    LanguageGo         ProgrammingLanguage = \"go\"\n    LanguageRust       ProgrammingLanguage = \"rust\"\n    LanguageJava       ProgrammingLanguage = \"java\"\n    LanguageCpp        ProgrammingLanguage = \"cpp\"\n)\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterSpec\n\nConfiguration for code execution environment.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    // Image is the container image to use for the interpreter sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n\n    // Language specifies the programming language for the interpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Language ProgrammingLanguage `json:\"language\"`\n\n    // RuntimeClassName specifies the runtime class for sandbox configuration.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    RuntimeClassName string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Storage defines persistent storage configuration for the interpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Storage *CodeInterpreterStorageSpec `json:\"storage,omitempty\"`\n\n    // SecurityContext defines pod-level security settings.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    SecurityContext *corev1.SecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n\n    // NetworkPolicy defines network isolation configuration.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    NetworkPolicy *CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec `json:\"networkPolicy,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds).\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:default=300\n    TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) for code execution.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n    // +kubebuilder:default=512\n    MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n\n    // AllowedImports defines the whitelist of allowed package imports.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=set\n    AllowedImports []string `json:\"allowedImports,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Env defines environment variables for the sandbox container.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=map\n    // +listMapKey=name\n    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterStorageSpec\n\nPersistent storage configuration.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterStorageSpec defines storage configuration for CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterStorageSpec struct {\n    // Size is the storage size (e.g., \"1Gi\", \"10Gi\").\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Size resource.Quantity `json:\"size\"`\n\n    // StorageClassName specifies the storage class for the volume.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    StorageClassName string `json:\"storageClassName,omitempty\"`\n\n    // AccessMode specifies the access mode for the volume.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=ReadWriteOnce;ReadOnlyMany;ReadWriteMany\n    // +kubebuilder:default=ReadWriteOnce\n    AccessMode string `json:\"accessMode,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec\n\nNetwork isolation configuration.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec defines network policy for CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec struct {\n    // IngressRules defines allowed ingress traffic.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=atomic\n    IngressRules []NetworkPolicyRule `json:\"ingressRules,omitempty\"`\n\n    // EgressRules defines allowed egress traffic.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=atomic\n    EgressRules []NetworkPolicyRule `json:\"egressRules,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// NetworkPolicyRule defines a network policy rule.\ntype NetworkPolicyRule struct {\n    // From specifies the source of traffic.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    From string `json:\"from,omitempty\"`\n\n    // To specifies the destination of traffic.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    To string `json:\"to,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Ports specifies the allowed ports.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=atomic\n    Ports []int32 `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterStatus\n\nObserved state of the CodeInterpreter.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Conditions represents the latest available observations.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +listType=map\n    // +listMapKey=type\n    // +patchMergeKey=type\n    // +patchStrategy=merge\n    Conditions []CodeInterpreterCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n\n    // InterpreterURL is the endpoint URL for the interpreter service.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    InterpreterURL string `json:\"interpreterURL,omitempty\"`\n\n    // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n\n    // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n    ExecutionCount int64 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n    ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterCondition\n\nCondition type for status reporting.\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterConditionType represents a condition type.\ntype CodeInterpreterConditionType string\n\nconst (\n    // CodeInterpreterConditionReady indicates the interpreter is ready.\n    CodeInterpreterConditionReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Ready\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterConditionStorageReady indicates storage is provisioned.\n    CodeInterpreterConditionStorageReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"StorageReady\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterConditionRuntimeReady indicates the runtime is ready.\n    CodeInterpreterConditionRuntimeReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"RuntimeReady\"\n\n    // CodeInterpreterConditionExecutionAvailable indicates execution is available.\n    CodeInterpreterConditionExecutionAvailable CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"ExecutionAvailable\"\n)\n\n// CodeInterpreterCondition represents a condition of a CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterCondition struct {\n    // Type is the type of the condition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Type CodeInterpreterConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n    Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n\n    // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message is a human-readable message.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Root Types\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Language\",type=string,JSONPath=`.spec.language`,description=\"Programming language\"\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n\n// CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n// A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Spec defines the desired state of the CodeInterpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Spec CodeInterpreterSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Status defines the observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n\n// CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpreterList struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Items is the list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Items []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### REST Resource Contract\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| API Group | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| Version | `v1alpha1` |\n| Kind | `CodeInterpreter` |\n| Plural | `codeinterpreters` |\n| Singular | `codeinterpreter` |\n| Short Names | `ci`, `cis` |\n| Scope | Namespaced |\n| Categories | `agentcube`, `all` |\n\n### HTTP Endpoints (Kubernetes API Server)\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n| POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n| PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Patch CodeInterpreter |\n| DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get Status subresource |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update Status subresource |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/codeinterpreters` | List all (cluster-scoped) |\n\n### Generated Client Interface\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpretersGetter provides access to CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpretersGetter interface {\n    CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n}\n\n// CodeInterpreterInterface provides CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    CodeInterpreterExpansion\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Rules\n\n| Field | Rule | Error Message |\n|-------|------|---------------|\n| `spec.image` | Required, MinLength=1 | `\"Image is required\"` |\n| `spec.language` | Required, Enum validation | `\"Invalid language\"` |\n| `spec.timeoutSeconds` | Minimum=1, Default=300 | `\"Timeout must be >= 1\"` |\n| `spec.maxMemoryMB` | Minimum=64, Default=512 | `\"Memory must be >= 64MB\"` |\n| `spec.storage.size` | Required if storage specified | `\"Storage size is required\"` |\n| `spec.storage.accessMode` | Enum: ReadWriteOnce/ReadOnlyMany/ReadWriteMany | `\"Invalid access mode\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Type-Level Errors\n\n1. **Validation Errors**: Kubernetes API server returns validation errors for invalid spec values\n2. **Scheme Registration Errors**: Runtime errors if types not properly registered\n3. **DeepCopy Errors**: Panic if DeepCopy methods not generated\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Source | Handling Strategy |\n|----------|--------|-------------------|\n| Schema Validation | Kubebuilder markers | API server rejects with 422 |\n| Type Conversion | runtime.Object interface | Compile-time checking |\n| Serialization | JSON marshaling | Return error to caller |\n| Code Generation | controller-gen | CI/CD failure, fix and regenerate |\n\n### Error Propagation\n\n```go\n// Example error handling pattern for client usage\nfunc (c *CodeInterpreterClient) SafeCreate(ctx context.Context, ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n    // Validate before sending\n    if err := validateCodeInterpreter(ci); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"validation failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    result, err := c.client.CodeInterpreters(ci.Namespace).Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        // Check for specific Kubernetes errors\n        if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n            return nil, ErrCodeInterpreterExists\n        }\n        if apierrors.IsInvalid(err) {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid spec: %w\", err)\n        }\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Type Definition Tests\n\nLocated in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc TestCodeInterpreterImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n    ci := &CodeInterpreter{}\n    var _ runtime.Object = ci // Compile-time assertion\n}\n\nfunc TestCodeInterpreterListImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n    list := &CodeInterpreterList{}\n    var _ runtime.Object = list // Compile-time assertion\n}\n\nfunc TestCodeInterpreterDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n    original := &CodeInterpreter{\n        Spec: CodeInterpreterSpec{\n            Image:    \"python:3.11\",\n            Language: LanguagePython,\n            TimeoutSeconds: func() *int32 { i := int32(300); return &i }(),\n        },\n    }\n\n    copied := original.DeepCopy()\n\n    // Verify copy is independent\n    *copied.Spec.TimeoutSeconds = 600\n    assert.Equal(t, int32(300), *original.Spec.TimeoutSeconds)\n}\n\nfunc TestProgrammingLanguageValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    validLanguages := []ProgrammingLanguage{\n        LanguagePython, LanguageJavaScript, LanguageTypeScript,\n        LanguageGo, LanguageRust, LanguageJava, LanguageCpp,\n    }\n\n    for _, lang := range validLanguages {\n        assert.NotEmpty(t, lang)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Scheme Registration Test\n\n```go\nfunc TestCodeInterpreterSchemeRegistration(t *testing.T) {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    err := v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Verify CodeInterpreter is registered\n    gv := v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion\n    gvk := gv.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n    obj, err := scheme.New(gvk)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.IsType(t, &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}, obj)\n}\n```\n\n### Code Generation Verification\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# verify-codegen.sh\n\n# Generate code\nmake generate\n\n# Verify compilation\ngo build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Verify tests pass\ngo test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Check no uncommitted changes\nif [[ -n $(git status --porcelain pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go) ]]; then\n    echo \"ERROR: DeepCopy methods not up to date\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Component | Coverage Target |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| Type definitions | 80%+ (struct validation) |\n| DeepCopy methods | Verified via generated code |\n| Scheme registration | 100% |\n| Client interfaces | Mock-based unit tests |\n\n### Continuous Integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/test.yaml\nname: Test\n\non: [push, pull_request]\n\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Set up Go\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n\n      - name: Verify code generation\n        run: make verify-generate\n\n      - name: Build\n        run: go build ./pkg/apis/...\n\n      - name: Test\n        run: go test -v -race ./pkg/apis/...\n\n      - name: Lint\n        uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v6\n        with:\n          version: latest\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_types.go      # CodeInterpreter type definitions (NEW)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime_types.go         # AgentRuntime type definitions (existing)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ register.go                   # Scheme registration (MODIFIED)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ doc.go                        # Package documentation\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ zz_generated.deepcopy.go      # Generated DeepCopy methods (GENERATED)\nв””в”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_types_test.go # Unit tests (NEW)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, runtime.Object |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | ResourceRequirements, EnvVar, SecurityContext |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource` | `v0.34.1` | Quantity for storage sizes |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools` | `v0.17.2` | controller-gen for code generation |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go generation |\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### 1. Separate CRD vs Extending AgentRuntime\n\n**Decision**: Create a separate `CodeInterpreter` CRD rather than extending `AgentRuntime`.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics focused on code execution\n- Independent RBAC and scheduling policies\n- Client-go library explicitly defines separate interfaces (`CodeInterpretersGetter` vs `AgentRuntimesGetter`)\n- Supports language-specific optimizations and security policies\n\n### 2. Controlled API Surface\n\n**Decision**: Define focused fields (`Image`, `Language`, `Resources`, `TimeoutSeconds`, etc.) rather than embedding full `PodSpec`.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Guides users toward code execution best practices\n- Simplifies API surface\n- Enables language-specific validation and defaults\n- Maintains consistency with `AgentRuntime` pattern\n\n### 3. Namespaced Scope\n\n**Decision**: CRD scope is `Namespaced`.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Aligns with multi-tenant Kubernetes patterns\n- Enables namespace-level quotas and isolation\n- Consistent with `AgentRuntime` scope\n\n### 4. Status Subresource\n\n**Decision**: Enable status subresource with `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Separation of concerns between spec and status\n- Enables RBAC to allow status updates without full object access\n- Standard Kubernetes pattern for controllers\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n- [Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n- [client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n\n| Version | Date | Changes |\n|---------|------|---------|\n| 1.0 | 2026-04-11 | Initial design for AR-002 CodeInterpreter CRD |\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775840770997,"end":1775840771007}}}}
